        "content": "<p>I want to show that two ideals of a semiring are equal knowing that are contained one to each other. I have an elementary proof, but I am sure it could be done more directly. </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Mathlib.RingTheory.Ideal.Operations</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Semiring</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">]{</span><span class=\"n\">I</span> <span class=\"n\">J</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Ideal</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">}(</span><span class=\"n\">hle</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span> <span class=\"bp\">≤</span> <span class=\"n\">J</span><span class=\"o\">)(</span><span class=\"n\">hre</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span> <span class=\"bp\">≥</span> <span class=\"n\">J</span><span class=\"o\">):</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"n\">J</span><span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n <span class=\"n\">ext</span>\n <span class=\"n\">exact</span> <span class=\"o\">⟨</span><span class=\"bp\">@</span><span class=\"n\">hle</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"bp\">@</span><span class=\"n\">hre</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">⟩</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
